li.p:
The graph shows the graphs of y = \abs{3x - 6} and y = 9. We see that there are two points on the graph of y = \abs{3x - 6} that have y = 9, and those points have x-coordinates x = -1 and x = 5. We can verify algebraically that the solutions are -1 and 5. 
    x \amp = \alert{-1}\text{: } 
        ~ ~ \abs{3(\alert{-1}) - 6} = \abs{-9} = 9
        x \amp = \alert{5}\text{: } 
        ~ ~ \abs{3(\alert{5}) - 6} = \abs{9} = 9

